Package leeLogger

Class Transactions

java.lang.Object
leeLogger.Transactions
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Transactions>
public class Transactions
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Transactions>
Class is used to produce objects of type transaction. Class implements Serializable and is used to create objects of transactions for the Banking application. These objects are used to recorde transactions by the user.
Author:
leefowler

  • Constructor Details

    • Transactions

      public Transactions​(boolean income, java.lang.String dateOfTransaction, java.lang.String title, double monetaryValue)
      Constructor makes the object of type Transaction with parameters that define the transactions. The income field is boolean to allow true (income) and false (expense).
      Parameters:
      income - boolean the type of the transaction (based on Enum class for INCOME and EXPENSE) true is INCOME, false is EXPENSE
      dateOfTransaction - String
      title - String title of the transaction eg. jeans or income
      monetaryValue - double this is the cost of the item
